    "what_description": "Vincetoxicum eurychiton is a perennial plant species belonging to the family Apocynaceae. It is characterized by its erect stems, which can grow up to 60 cm in height, and its ovate, pointed leaves that are 5-10 cm long and 2-4 cm wide. The leaves are oppositely arranged and have a leathery texture. The plant produces greenish-white flowers in a raceme, with each flower being 1.5-2.5 cm long and having a five-lobed corolla. The flowers are pollinated by bees and other insects, and the plant is native to the mountainous regions of eastern Asia.",
