    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Vincetoxicum eurychiton are alkaloids including eurychitonine and vincamine which exhibit vasodilatory properties by blocking calcium channels thus improving blood circulation. Cytotoxic compounds like eurychitomin and vincamine analogs possess anti-proliferative and pro-apoptotic effects against cancer cells by interfering with DNA replication and cell cycle progression. Flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol demonstrate antioxidant activity by scavenging free radicals and inhibiting lipid peroxidation. Iridoid glycosides like aucubin and catalpol show anti-inflammatory effects by suppressing the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Additionally, the plant's phenolic acids like caffeic acid and ferulic acid contribute to its antioxidant and antimicrobial properties.",
