    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Vincetoxicum eurychiton are vincetoxicum tincture, infusion, vincetoxicum infusion, and decoction. These preparations are typically made from the leaves and stems of the plant, which are rich in diterpenoids and iridoid glycosides. Vincetoxicum tincture is a concentrated liquid extract of the plant, often used in homeopathy and traditional medicine. Infusion and vincetoxicum infusion are liquid preparations made by steeping the plant material in hot water, with infusion being a general term and vincetoxicum infusion specifically referring to the plant. Decoction is a more intense liquid preparation made by boiling the plant material in water, often used to extract the plant's alkaloids and glycosides.",
